 the rowing team shone at the Olympics, but a gold shortage saw Team GB relegated to seventh.\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 1032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 810, \"end\": 817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.999601930649529, \"rank\": 0.0002575039529845802, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}, {\"begin\": 884, \"end\": 889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999691569200796, \"rank\": 1.844981155596986e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 915, \"end\": 925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkinson_Minerals_Area\", \"score\": 0.8805017896297221, \"rank\": 0.13571603349107322, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkinson_Minerals_Area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkinson_Minerals_Area\"}, {\"begin\": 927, \"end\": 935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Yee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\"}, {\"begin\": 1003, \"end\": 1010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999873277381848, \"rank\": 1.2493566717000409e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few weeks earlier, England's men footballers went agonisingly close again to a first major trophy since 1966.\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1055, \"end\": 1062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9998174169711093, \"rank\": 0.0001762206730154895, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They scraped through the rounds at the European Championship in Germany, making it all the way to the final, where they were narrowly beaten 2-1 by Spain.\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1211, \"end\": 1218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999894457688, \"rank\": 1.0554023088744905e-08, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1295, \"end\": 1300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.284634219844849e-15, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite a major tournament consistency unmatched by any of his predecessors, Gareth Southgate decided the time was right to step down, and German Thomas Tuchel is the man tasked with trying to go one better at the World Cup in 2026.\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1380, \"end\": 1396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gareth_Southgate\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gareth Southgate\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gareth_Southgate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gareth_Southgate\"}, {\"begin\": 1442, \"end\": 1448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.9407060079753107, \"rank\": 0.05582543122874608, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1449, \"end\": 1462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Tuchel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Tuchel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Tuchel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Tuchel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the club game, Manchester City hit another milestone with an unprecedented fourth Premier League title in a row, but, despite the boost of Pep Guardiola signing a new deal, they have their work cut out if they are to challenge for a fifth.\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1555, \"end\": 1570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_City_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9997079323445511, \"rank\": 0.000292152983738353, \"text\": \"Manchester City\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_City_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_City_F.C.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Emma Hayes topped the Women's Super League again with Chelsea before taking up a new challenge across the Atlantic and leading the United States to Olympic gold, while there was another league and cup double in Scotland for Celtic.\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 2012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1781, \"end\": 1791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hayes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma Hayes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Hayes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http