: []}, {\"sentence\": \"Andy Murray andRafael Nadalboth admitted defeat in their battles against their own bodies, with Murray given a tearful send-off at Wimbledon before some trademark never-say-die heroics at the Olympics alongside Dan Evans.\", \"from\": 2119, \"to\": 2340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2119, \"end\": 2130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.6245321794632e-60, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 2215, \"end\": 2221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.104019766725893e-33, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 2330, \"end\": 2339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Die_Warzau\", \"score\": 0.609780165904922, \"rank\": 0.6399352683370019, \"text\": \"Dan Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Die_Warzau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Die_Warzau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics was also a key target for Nadal, who fell short of a medal alongside Carlos Alcaraz before deciding to call it a day on home soil in the Davis Cup.\", \"from\": 2342, \"to\": 2502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2381, \"end\": 2386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 0.9999999949641278, \"rank\": 5.035865835509051e-09, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 2424, \"end\": 2438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alcaraz won two more grand slam titles, emulating his hero with a French Open-Wimbledon double, but the player of the season was undoubtedly Jannik Sinner, who won his first two slam trophies and is a clear world number one, although the doping case still hanging over him has left a sour taste.\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2504, \"end\": 2511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.988732122020326e-20, \"text\": \"Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\"}, {\"begin\": 2645, \"end\": 2658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jannik_Sinner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jannik Sinner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jannik_Sinner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jannik_Sinner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Novak Djokovic claimed a long-awaited Olympic gold before hiring Murray as coach to set up one of the most anticipated stories of 2025.\", \"from\": 2801, \"to\": 2936, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2801, \"end\": 2815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Novak Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 2866, \"end\": 2872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.104019766725893e-33, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was disappointment for England's men and women cricketers in their respective T20 World Cups.\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 3037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2967, \"end\": 2974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9998174169711093, \"rank\": 0.0001762206730154895, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men made a decent defence of their title but were knocked out by India in the semi-finals, while the women were unable to make it out of the group stage.\", \"from\": 3039, \"to\": 3196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3108, \"end\": 3113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999998458406, \"rank\": 1.541644799297267e-10, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The standout moment of the year came in the Test arena in October when Joe Root overtook Sir Alastair Cook to become England's highest Test run-scorer of all time.\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3269, \"end\": 3272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"score\": 0.9984240487897041, \"rank\": 0.001577879245401715, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\"}, {\"begin\": 3287, \"end\": 3304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alastair_Cook\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 